<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Blackstone (BX)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Blackstone Inc. — using actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated {meta.published} · Data: Latest Annual/TTM</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- VERDICT -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${fetchedPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- METRICS -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${rawRev[0] !== undefined ? (rawRev[0] / 1000).toFixed(1) : 'N/A'}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(fcf2024 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${rawEps[0] !== undefined ? rawEps[0].toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model. No multiples, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Blackstone generated <strong>${(fcf2024 / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>12% per year</strong> for 5 years. A robust projection anticipating capital deployments and realization performance over a typical cycle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>3.5% forever</strong>. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>10%</strong> — our required rate of return. This comfortably clears the 10Y Treasury (4.18%) plus a reasonable equity risk premium.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(2)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ASSUMPTIONS -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>Here are the explicit drivers of our model for BX.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">12%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Blackstone's immense scale and shift toward perpetual capital vehicles supply structurally growing management fees. Performance fees and realizations can be lumpy, but a blended 12% FCF CAGR maps reasonably to their asset gathering velocity.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">10%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        With the 10Y Treasury at 4.18%, we apply an equity risk premium that settles at a firm 10% hurdle rate. It reflects the inherent volatility of carried interest compared to pure fee-related earnings.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">3.5%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Assumes long-term nominal GDP growth plus slight inflation/premium dynamics. As the dominant alternative asset manager globally, BX should outgrow the general economy marginally into perpetuity.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FCF TABLE -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (Year 0)</td>
          <td>${fcf2024.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map((p, i) => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- TERMINAL VALUE -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF (Year 5 × 1.035)</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value (FCF₆ ÷ (10% − 3.5%))</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- FINAL CALCULATION -->
  <h3>Final Valuation</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>+ Net Cash (Cash − Debt)</td>
          <td>${netCash.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>= Equity Value</td>
          <td>${equityValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>÷ Shares Outstanding</td>
          <td>{sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- CHARTS -->
  <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>

  <h3>Revenue ($M)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {revenueHistory.map(r => (
      r.value !== null ? (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${(r.value / Math.max(...rawRev.filter(v=>v!==null))) * 100}%`}>
            ${r.value.toLocaleString()}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      ) : null
    ))}
  </div>

  <h3>Free Cash Flow ($M)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {fcfHistory.map(r => (
      r.value !== null ? (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill fcf" style={`width: ${(r.value / Math.max(...rawFcf.filter(v=>v!==null))) * 100}%`}>
            ${r.value.toLocaleString()}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      ) : null
    ))}
  </div>

  <h3>Earnings Per Share (Diluted)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {epsHistory.map(r => (
      r.value !== null ? (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill eps" style={`width: ${(Math.max(0.1, r.value) / Math.max(...rawEps.filter(v=>v!==null))) * 100}%`}>
            ${r.value.toFixed(2)}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      ) : null
    ))}
  </div>

  <!-- SENSITIVITY -->
  <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="sensitivity-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
          {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
            <th class={g === growthRatePhase1 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(0)}%</th>
          ))}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
          <tr>
            <td>{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(0)}%</td>
            {row.values.map((v, i) => (
              <td class={row.dr === discountRate && sensitivityGrowth[i] === growthRatePhase1 ? 'current' : ''}>
                ${v}
              </td>
            ))}
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- RISKS -->
  <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>
  <h3>Upside Risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Perpetual Capital Acceleration:</strong> Continued success in retail and private wealth channels capturing permanent, stickier capital with lucrative fee structures.</li>
    <li><strong>Interest Rate Relief:</strong> Lower rates typically stimulate transaction volumes, unlocking carried interest and driving performance revenues higher than standard linear models predict.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Downside Risks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Real Estate Headwinds:</strong> Extended structural declines in commercial real estate valuation could drag heavily on realizations and performance fees.</li>
    <li><strong>Fundraising Plateaus:</strong> A macro shock or sustained high-rate environment could cause institutional allocators to pull back or pause new commitments.</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why is Net Cash negative?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Blackstone operates with leverage. Their Total Debt (${totalDebt.toLocaleString()}M) exceeds their Cash & Equivalents (${cashAndInvestments.toLocaleString()}M). This net debt is standard for alternative asset managers structuring their balance sheets efficiently.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How does carried interest impact FCF?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Unlike fee-related earnings (FRE), carried interest (performance fees) is highly variable. While it causes FCF to be lumpy from year to year, over a 5-year cycle smoothed into a 12% CAGR, it captures the average long-term realization pace.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

